text: S&P futures opened up evening session +28 handles .... now +11 handles - my updated market view coming up tomorrow on @realmoney @Seabreezelp @dougkass

@dougkass @SeabreezeLP From Goldman Sachs Research $TSLA Tesla: 4Q22 deliveries up 31% yoy to about 405k but below consensus 2 January 2023 | 6:09PM EST Tesla reported preliminary 4Q22 vehicle deliveries of about 405k (up 18% qoq and up 31% yoy), and production of about

440k vehicles. Deliveries were below the now lower Bloomberg consensus at about 421k (note that consensus as of early December was about 430k) and GSe at 420k, and we believe below buyside consensus. We consider the 4Q report to be an incremental negative, although we continue

to see Tesla as well positioned for long-term growth given its position as a cost and full solution leader in clean mobility/EVs (a market that we expect to exhibit significant long-term growth) and we maintain our Buy rating on the stock. We believe key debates from here will

be on whether vehicle deliveries can reaccelerate (we expect that they will especially starting in 2Q23), margins (and how much lower costs can offset lower prices), and Tesla's brand (and it being associated clearly with its leadership position in clean mobility/EVs).
